<recipe>
  <name>Sausage Seasoning</name>
  <safe_name>Sausage_Seasoning</safe_name>
  <yield_count></yield_count>
  <yield_measure></yield_measure>
  <notes>I'm a fan of fresh turkey sausage patties but finding ones that have any flavor in the store is a non-starter.  After several months of tinkering around trying to concoct my own recipe I cracked open Joy and found their seasoning to be mighty tasty with a little tinkering.  The trimmings from a normally butchered set of spareribs makes some truly excellent ground pork suitable for grilling with this recipe</notes>
  <prep_time></prep_time>
  <ingredients>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>1 1/2 lbs</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>ground pork or turkey</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>2 tsp</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>coarsly ground black pepper</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>1 1/2 tsp</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>dried sage</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>1 tsp </quantity>
      <ingredient_name>salt</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>1/2 tsp</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>dried marjoram</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>1/4 tsp</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>dried savory or thyme</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>pinch</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>ground ginger</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>pinch or two</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>ground red pepper</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
  </ingredients>
  <preparation>Place ground meat in a large bowl.  Combine dry ingredients and integrate into meat, tossing with a fork to ensure even coverage before forming patties.</preparation>
